detailed_description: A Python-based distributed molecular docking system that supports parallel computation across multiple nodes to improve the efficiency of virtual screening campaigns.

name: PoseX
one_line_profile: Benchmark dataset for molecular docking
detailed_description: A benchmark suite designed for evaluating molecular docking algorithms and pose prediction accuracy.

name: Vina-GPU
one_line_profile: OpenCL implementation of AutoDock Vina for GPU acceleration
detailed_description: A heterogeneous OpenCL implementation of AutoDock Vina designed to accelerate molecular docking simulations using GPU hardware.

name: Vina-GPU-2.0
one_line_profile: Accelerated AutoDock Vina and QuickVina on GPUs
detailed_description: The second version of Vina-GPU, accelerating AutoDock Vina and derived methods like QuickVina 2 and QuickVina-W using GPU parallelization.

name: Vina-GPU-2.1
one_line_profile: Improved GPU docking toolkit for virtual screening
detailed_description: An updated version of the Vina-GPU toolkit offering faster speeds and higher accuracy for large-scale virtual screening campaigns.

name: DockM8
one_line_profile: Consensus docking workflow for virtual screening
detailed_description: An all-in-one Structure-Based Virtual Screening (SBVS) workflow that implements consensus docking strategies to improve hit enrichment.

name: GeoDock
one_line_profile: Flexible protein-protein docking with iterative transformer
detailed_description: A deep learning model for flexible protein-protein docking that uses a multi-track iterative transformer to predict complex structures.

name: DiffBindFR
one_line_profile: Diffusion model for flexible protein-ligand docking
detailed_description: A diffusion model-based method for protein-ligand flexible docking, enabling the exploration of ligand binding poses with receptor flexibility.

name: Vina-CUDA
one_line_profile: CUDA-accelerated AutoDock Vina
detailed_description: An implementation of AutoDock Vina optimized for NVIDIA GPUs using CUDA, providing significant speedups for docking simulations.

name: EquiBind
one_line_profile: Geometric deep learning for binding structure prediction
detailed_description: A geometric deep learning model for fast and direct prediction of receptor-ligand complex structures without heavy sampling.

name: FlowSite
one_line_profile: Flow matching for multi-ligand docking and site design
detailed_description: Implementation of HarmonicFlow and FlowSite for harmonic self-conditioned flow matching, enabling multi-ligand docking and binding site design.

name: DeepVS
one_line_profile: Deep learning approach for docking-based virtual screening
detailed_description: A deep learning framework designed to improve the performance of docking-based virtual screening by learning from protein-ligand complexes.

name: Confidence Bootstrapping
one_line_profile: Confidence bootstrapping procedure for protein-ligand docking
detailed_description: An implementation of the Confidence Bootstrapping protocol to enhance the reliability of protein-ligand docking predictions.

name: GetBox-PyMOL-Plugin
one_line_profile: PyMOL plugin to calculate docking boxes for LeDock, AutoDock, and Vina
detailed_description: A PyMOL plugin designed to assist in the preparation of molecular docking simulations by calculating and visualizing the docking box dimensions and coordinates for popular docking engines like LeDock, AutoDock, and AutoDock Vina.

name: DockStream
one_line_profile: Docking wrapper to enhance de novo molecular design workflows
detailed_description: DockStream provides a unified interface to various molecular docking engines, facilitating their integration into de novo molecular design and generative modeling workflows. It abstracts the complexity of different docking backends.

name: MzDOCK
one_line_profile: Automated GUI-based pipeline for molecular docking
detailed_description: MzDOCK is a graphical user interface (GUI) pipeline designed to automate the molecular docking process, making it accessible for users to perform ligand-receptor docking tasks without extensive command-line usage.

name: FlexAID
one_line_profile: Flexible Artificial Intelligence Docking software
detailed_description: FlexAID is a molecular docking program that uses a genetic algorithm for conformational search and allows for receptor flexibility. It is designed to predict the binding pose of small molecules to protein targets.

name: cuEquivariance
one_line_profile: CUDA-accelerated library for equivariant neural networks in science
detailed_description: cuEquivariance is a high-performance mathematical library providing primitives and tensor operations to accelerate equivariant neural networks (e.g., DiffDock, MACE, Allegro) used in molecular modeling and structure prediction.

name: DSDP
one_line_profile: Deep Site and Docking Pose blind docking strategy
detailed_description: DSDP (Deep Site and Docking Pose) is a GPU-accelerated blind docking strategy that integrates deep learning-based binding site prediction with a modified AutoDock Vina-based pose sampling algorithm.

name: DSDPFlex
one_line_profile: Flexible-receptor docking with GPU acceleration
detailed_description: DSDPFlex is an extension of the DSDP docking tool that incorporates receptor flexibility into the docking process, utilizing GPU acceleration to handle the increased computational complexity.

name: qvina
one_line_profile: Accelerated version of AutoDock Vina
detailed_description: QVina (QuickVina) is a fork of AutoDock Vina that provides significant speedups for molecular docking calculations without sacrificing accuracy, optimized for high-throughput virtual screening.

name: FABind
one_line_profile: Fast and Accurate Protein-Ligand Binding prediction
detailed_description: FABind is a deep learning model for predicting protein-ligand binding structures. It optimizes the docking process by jointly modeling the protein-ligand interaction and conformation.

name: gnina-torch
one_line_profile: PyTorch implementation of GNINA scoring function
detailed_description: gnina-torch provides a PyTorch implementation of the CNN-based scoring functions used in GNINA, allowing for easy integration into deep learning workflows and gradient-based optimization.

name: LABODOCK
one_line_profile: Colab-based molecular docking tools
detailed_description: LABODOCK is a collection of Google Colab notebooks and scripts that facilitate running molecular docking simulations (using Vina, etc.) in the cloud, making high-performance docking accessible without local resources.

name: MolecularDocking
one_line_profile: Collection of notebooks and tools for molecular docking
detailed_description: A repository containing Jupyter notebooks and scripts to perform and analyze molecular docking simulations, serving as a lightweight workflow for educational and research purposes.

name: HASTEN
one_line_profile: Machine Learning Boosted Docking for virtual screening
detailed_description: HASTEN is a tool that accelerates structure-based virtual screening by using machine learning to predict docking scores, reducing the number of full docking calculations required.

name: AMDock
one_line_profile: Assisted molecular docking with AutoDock4 and AutoDock Vina
detailed_description: AMDock is a user-friendly tool that facilitates the molecular docking process using AutoDock4 and AutoDock Vina. It provides a graphical interface and helper scripts to streamline preparation, execution, and analysis.

name: AMDock-win
one_line_profile: Windows version of AMDock for assisted molecular docking
detailed_description: The Windows-specific distribution of AMDock, providing the same assisted molecular docking capabilities for AutoDock4 and AutoDock Vina on Windows systems.

name: RNAxplorer
one_line_profile: Tool to explore RNA conformation space
detailed_description: RNAxplorer is a tool from the ViennaRNA group designed to explore RNA conformational space through sampling techniques, aiding in the study of RNA structure and dynamics.

name: CADD-Scripts
one_line_profile: Scripts for virtual screening, cross docking, and protein relaxation
detailed_description: A comprehensive collection of shell scripts and utilities for automating common Computer-Aided Drug Design (CADD) tasks, including virtual screening, cross-docking, and protein structure preparation using Schrdinger and Rosetta.

name: VinaLC
one_line_profile: Parallel molecular docking program based on AutoDock Vina
detailed_description: VinaLC is a parallelized version of AutoDock Vina developed by LLNL, designed for high-performance computing environments to accelerate large-scale molecular docking campaigns.

name: Physics-aware-Multiplex-GNN
one_line_profile: Geometric deep learning framework for molecular systems
detailed_description: Implementation of a physics-aware multiplex Graph Neural Network (GNN) for accurate and efficient geometric deep learning on molecular systems, applicable to property prediction and interaction modeling.

name: PackDock
one_line_profile: Diffusion-based side chain packing model for flexible protein-ligand docking
detailed_description: PackDock is a diffusion-based model designed to tackle the challenge of flexible protein-ligand docking by incorporating side chain packing. It aims to predict accurate binding poses by modeling the flexibility of protein side chains during the docking process.

name: FDA
one_line_profile: Folding-Docking-Affinity framework for protein-ligand affinity prediction
detailed_description: FDA (Folding-Docking-Affinity) is a framework that integrates protein folding, molecular docking, and affinity prediction into a unified pipeline. It is designed to predict protein-ligand binding affinities starting from sequence information.

name: DockCoV2
one_line_profile: Molecular docking pipeline for SARS-CoV-2 drug discovery
detailed_description: DockCoV2 is a molecular docking pipeline specifically designed for screening drug databases against SARS-CoV-2 targets. It facilitates the identification of potential therapeutic candidates for COVID-19.

name: REstretto
one_line_profile: Fragment-based protein-ligand docking tool
detailed_description: REstretto (REuse of sub-STRuctures as an Effective Technique for protein-ligand docking TOol) is a virtual screening-oriented docking tool that utilizes fragment reuse techniques to improve docking efficiency and accuracy.

name: QuickBind
one_line_profile: Lightweight and interpretable molecular docking model
detailed_description: QuickBind is a molecular docking model designed to be both lightweight and interpretable. It aims to provide efficient binding pose predictions while offering insights into the docking process.

name: dockit
one_line_profile: High-throughput molecular docking pipeline for Vina engines
detailed_description: dockit is a Python-based tool for high-throughput molecular docking. It supports multiple targets and ligands and is designed to work with Vina series docking engines, facilitating large-scale virtual screening campaigns.

name: DiffSBDD
one_line_profile: Euclidean diffusion model for structure-based drug design
detailed_description: DiffSBDD is a Euclidean diffusion model specifically developed for structure-based drug design (SBDD). It generates ligand structures that fit into protein binding pockets, leveraging diffusion processes for molecule generation.

name: SAnDReS
one_line_profile: Statistical analysis environment for docking results and scoring functions
detailed_description: SAnDReS (Statistical Analysis of Docking Results and Scoring functions) is a computational environment for developing and analyzing machine-learning models to predict ligand-binding affinity. It provides tools for statistical analysis of docking outcomes.

name: metascreener
one_line_profile: Integration script collection for docking and virtual screening
detailed_description: metascreener is a collection of scripts designed to integrate various docking, virtual screening, similarity search, and molecular modeling programs into a cohesive workflow for drug discovery.

name: watvina
one_line_profile: AutoDock Vina fork with explicit/implicit water models
detailed_description: watvina is a modified version of the AutoDock Vina engine that incorporates implicit or explicit water models to improve docking accuracy. It also supports pharmacophore and position-constrained docking.

name: Scalar Fields
one_line_profile: Equivariant scalar fields for molecular docking with FFT
detailed_description: This tool implements Equivariant Scalar Fields for molecular docking, utilizing Fast Fourier Transforms (FFT) to accelerate the docking process while maintaining equivariance properties.

name: Animal-in-Motion
one_line_profile: Pipeline for animal video data processing and pose prediction
detailed_description: Animal-in-Motion is a data collection and processing pipeline for animal videos. It includes annotations for masks, keypoints, depth, and occlusion, suitable for 3D/4D reconstruction, tracking, and pose prediction in biological research.

name: Protenix-Dock
one_line_profile: End-to-end trainable protein-ligand docking framework
detailed_description: Protenix-Dock is an accurate and trainable end-to-end framework for protein-ligand docking. It leverages deep learning to predict binding poses directly.

name: CarsiDock
one_line_profile: Deep learning paradigm for accurate protein-ligand docking
detailed_description: CarsiDock is a deep learning-based tool for accurate protein-ligand docking and screening. It utilizes large-scale pre-training to improve prediction performance.

name: AutoDock Vina
one_line_profile: Standard open-source molecular docking engine
detailed_description: AutoDock Vina is one of the most widely used open-source programs for molecular docking. It significantly improves the average accuracy of the binding mode predictions compared to AutoDock 4.

name: CReM-dock
one_line_profile: Docking-guided chemical generation tool
detailed_description: CReM-dock is a tool for generating chemically reasonable molecules guided by molecular docking scores. It combines chemical generation with structure-based evaluation.

name: DeepDock
one_line_profile: Deep learning package for molecular docking
detailed_description: DeepDock is an experimental package from DeepChem that applies deep learning techniques to molecular docking tasks, aiming to improve prediction accuracy over traditional methods.

name: dockstring
one_line_profile: Python package for molecular docking with curated datasets and benchmarking capabilities
detailed_description: dockstring is a Python package that facilitates molecular docking tasks by providing a simple interface to the AutoDock Vina engine, coupled with a highly curated dataset for benchmarking and regression tasks in drug discovery.

name: Uni-Dock
one_line_profile: GPU-accelerated molecular docking program
detailed_description: Uni-Dock is a high-performance, GPU-accelerated molecular docking software developed by DP Technology. It is designed to speed up the virtual screening process significantly compared to traditional CPU-based methods.

name: Uni-Dock2
one_line_profile: Next-generation GPU-accelerated molecular docking software
detailed_description: Uni-Dock 2 is the successor to Uni-Dock, offering enhanced performance and features for GPU-accelerated molecular docking in drug discovery pipelines.

name: LigGrep
one_line_profile: Tool for filtering docked poses based on receptor-ligand interactions
detailed_description: LigGrep is a command-line tool designed to analyze and filter molecular docking results. It identifies docked poses that participate in specific user-defined receptor-ligand interactions, aiding in the selection of promising candidates.

name: MolModa
one_line_profile: Browser-based molecular docking environment
detailed_description: MolModa is a web-based platform that allows users to perform molecular docking entirely within their web browser, leveraging WebAssembly technologies to run docking engines locally.

name: Webina
one_line_profile: JavaScript/WebAssembly library for running AutoDock Vina in the browser
detailed_description: Webina is a library that ports AutoDock Vina to WebAssembly, enabling molecular docking calculations to run directly in a web browser on the client side.

name: Ringtail
one_line_profile: Analysis and storage package for virtual screenings with AutoDock
detailed_description: Ringtail is a Python package developed by the Forli Lab for managing, storing, and analyzing large-scale virtual screening results generated by AutoDock-GPU and AutoDock Vina.

name: DiffDock
one_line_profile: Diffusion generative model for molecular docking
detailed_description: DiffDock is a state-of-the-art deep learning framework that uses diffusion generative models to predict the 3D structure of protein-ligand complexes (molecular docking) with high accuracy.

name: DisCo-DiffDock
one_line_profile: Enhanced diffusion model for molecular docking with discrete latents
detailed_description: DisCo-DiffDock is an extension of the DiffDock model that incorporates discrete latents to enhance the continuous diffusion process for molecular docking tasks.

name: GNINA
one_line_profile: Deep learning framework for molecular docking
detailed_description: GNINA is a molecular docking software that utilizes deep convolutional neural networks to score protein-ligand poses, providing an alternative to traditional empirical scoring functions.

name: Phinder
one_line_profile: Pharmacophore feature identification using GNINA
detailed_description: Phinder is a tool for the semi-automatic identification of pharmacophore features from unbound receptor structures using GNINA fragment docking.

name: DrugHIVE
one_line_profile: Deep hierarchical generative model for structure-based drug design
detailed_description: DrugHIVE is a deep generative model designed for structure-based drug design (SBDD). It utilizes a hierarchical approach to generate small molecule structures that fit within specific protein binding pockets.

name: IDPConformerGenerator
one_line_profile: Conformational sampling tool for Intrinsically Disordered Proteins
detailed_description: A tool developed by the Forman-Kay Lab to build conformational representations of Intrinsically Disordered Proteins (IDPs) and Regions (IDRs) through guided sampling of protein torsion space.

name: autoparty
one_line_profile: Machine learning-guided visual inspection tool for molecular docking
detailed_description: Autoparty is a tool from Keiser Lab that assists in the visual inspection of molecular docking results using machine learning guidance, helping to prioritize poses for manual review.

name: DiffDock-PP
one_line_profile: Rigid Protein-Protein Docking using Diffusion Models
detailed_description: DiffDock-PP is a deep learning method for rigid protein-protein docking that leverages diffusion models to predict the docked complex structure.

name: LightDock
one_line_profile: Macromolecular docking framework based on the Glowworm Swarm Optimization algorithm
detailed_description: LightDock is a protein-protein, protein-peptide, and protein-DNA docking framework that uses the Glowworm Swarm Optimization (GSO) algorithm. It supports flexible docking and is highly scalable.

name: LightDock (Python 2.7)
one_line_profile: Legacy Python 2.7 version of the LightDock docking framework
detailed_description: This is the legacy Python 2.7 implementation of the LightDock macromolecular docking framework. While the main version has moved to Python 3, this repo is maintained for compatibility or reference.

name: LightDock-Rust
one_line_profile: Rust implementation of the LightDock docking software
detailed_description: A Rust port of the LightDock macromolecular docking software, aiming for performance improvements and memory safety provided by the Rust language.

name: Dockey
one_line_profile: Integrated workflow tool for molecular docking and virtual screening
detailed_description: Dockey is an integrated tool designed to streamline molecular docking and virtual screening workflows. It automates ligand preparation, docking execution, and result analysis.

name: Str2Str
one_line_profile: Score-based framework for zero-shot protein conformation sampling
detailed_description: Str2Str is a score-based generative framework for sampling protein conformations in a zero-shot manner, enabling the exploration of protein structural diversity without extensive training on specific targets.

name: 3D-Generative-SBDD
one_line_profile: 3D Generative Model for Structure-Based Drug Design
detailed_description: A deep learning model for generating 3D molecular structures conditioned on protein binding sites, designed for structure-based drug design applications.

name: TankBind
one_line_profile: Deep learning model for protein-ligand binding structure prediction
detailed_description: TankBind is a deep learning model that predicts protein-ligand binding structures and affinities. It treats the binding pocket as a 'tank' to capture interactions.

name: Plantain
one_line_profile: Molecular docking tool with AI-based pose scoring function
detailed_description: Plantain is a molecular docking tool that integrates an artificial intelligence-based scoring function to improve the accuracy of pose prediction and virtual screening.

name: EquiDock
one_line_profile: Geometric deep learning model for fast rigid 3D protein-protein docking
detailed_description: An SE(3)-equivariant geometric deep learning model designed to predict the complex structure of two proteins by performing rigid body docking.

name: Boltzina
one_line_profile: Docking-guided binding prediction tool for virtual screening
detailed_description: A virtual screening tool that combines docking with deep learning-based binding prediction (Boltz-2) to achieve efficient and accurate identification of active compounds.

name: DockingPie
one_line_profile: PyMOL plugin for consensus docking and result analysis
detailed_description: A plugin for PyMOL that integrates various docking programs (Vina, RxDock, etc.) to perform consensus docking and analyze binding modes within a graphical interface.

name: ab_opt
one_line_profile: Generative diffusion models for antibody design and docking
detailed_description: Implementation of generative diffusion models specifically tailored for the design, docking, and optimization of antibodies.

name: DiffDock-Pocket
one_line_profile: Diffusion model for pocket-level docking with side chain flexibility
detailed_description: An extension of DiffDock that focuses on pocket-level docking and incorporates side chain flexibility for more accurate protein-ligand binding predictions.

name: runs-n-poses
one_line_profile: Benchmark dataset for protein-ligand co-folding prediction
detailed_description: A curated benchmark dataset designed to evaluate models for protein-ligand co-folding and interaction prediction.

name: PandaDock
one_line_profile: Physics-based molecular docking tool
detailed_description: A Python-based molecular docking tool that utilizes physics-based scoring functions to predict ligand binding poses.

name: PyPLIF-HIPPOS
one_line_profile: Molecular interaction fingerprinting tool for docking results
detailed_description: A tool for generating protein-ligand interaction fingerprints (PLIF) from docking results produced by AutoDock Vina and PLANTS, facilitating post-docking analysis.

name: screenlamp
one_line_profile: Toolkit for hypothesis-driven virtual screening
detailed_description: A Python toolkit designed to facilitate hypothesis-driven virtual screening workflows, allowing for customized filtering and selection of ligand candidates.

name: siteinterlock
one_line_profile: Graph-based pose selection for protein-ligand docking
detailed_description: A tool that applies graph theory to improve pose selection in protein-ligand docking, aiming to identify the most probable binding conformations.

name: FABFlex
one_line_profile: Fast and accurate blind flexible docking model
detailed_description: Official implementation of the ICLR 2025 paper 'Fast and Accurate Blind Flexible Docking', providing a deep learning model for flexible protein-ligand docking.

name: dockECR
one_line_profile: Consensus docking and ranking protocol for virtual screening
detailed_description: An open protocol for consensus docking and ranking of small molecules, designed to improve the reliability of virtual screening campaigns.

name: gdock
one_line_profile: Genetic algorithm-based protein-protein docking tool
detailed_description: A protein-protein docking application implemented in Rust that utilizes genetic algorithms for conformational search.

name: docking_py
one_line_profile: Python library for automating molecular docking with Vina/Smina
detailed_description: A Python library that simplifies the automation and scripting of molecular docking tasks using Smina, Vina, and their variants.

name: VSDS-VD
one_line_profile: Benchmarking framework for AI-powered docking methods in virtual screening
detailed_description: A repository for benchmarking AI-powered docking methods specifically from the perspective of virtual screening, providing datasets and evaluation scripts.

name: Auto_AutoDock-GPU
one_line_profile: Batch processing tools for high-throughput protein-ligand docking with AutoDock-GPU
detailed_description: A set of tools designed to facilitate high-throughput protein-ligand docking in batch mode utilizing the AutoDock-GPU engine.

name: AutoDock VinaXB
one_line_profile: AutoDock Vina variant with halogen bond scoring function (XBSF)
detailed_description: An implementation of XBSF, a new empirical halogen bond scoring function, integrated into AutoDock Vina to improve docking accuracy for halogenated ligands.

name: VS-autodock-vina
one_line_profile: AutoDock Vina extension for virtual screening analysis
detailed_description: A modified version of AutoDock Vina that adds functionality specifically for analyzing virtual screening results.

name: mvina
one_line_profile: Modified version of AutoDock Vina for Linux
detailed_description: A modified implementation of the AutoDock Vina docking engine, optimized for Linux environments.

name: VinaSH
one_line_profile: AutoDock Vina variant accounting for Sigma Hole interactions
detailed_description: An improved version of AutoDock Vina that incorporates Sigma Hole interactions into the scoring function for better docking accuracy.

name: DiffDock (Colab)
one_line_profile: Colab implementation of the DiffDock molecular docking model
detailed_description: A Jupyter Notebook/Colab implementation of DiffDock, a diffusion generative model for molecular docking, enabling researchers to run the tool in cloud environments.

name: FlexPose
one_line_profile: AI-based framework for flexible protein-ligand binding pose modeling
detailed_description: A framework for AI-based flexible modeling of protein-ligand binding poses, addressing the flexibility of both ligand and protein during docking.

name: FlexDock
one_line_profile: Flexible docking and relaxation using composed unbalanced flows
detailed_description: Implementation of a method for flexible docking and relaxation by composing unbalanced flows, as presented at ICLR 2025.

name: ProQDock
one_line_profile: Support Vector Regression based protein-protein docking scoring program
detailed_description: A scoring program for protein-protein docking that uses high-level coordinate-driven features and a Support Vector Regression algorithm to evaluate docking models.

name: FeatureDock
one_line_profile: Transformer-based protein-ligand docking software
detailed_description: A protein-ligand docking software guided by physicochemical feature-based local environment learning using Transformer architecture.

name: IGModel
one_line_profile: Simultaneous prediction of ligand docking pose RMSD and binding strength
detailed_description: A deep learning model capable of simultaneously predicting the RMSD of a ligand docking pose and its binding strength against the target protein.

name: OnionNet-SFCT
one_line_profile: Scoring function correction term for protein-ligand docking
detailed_description: A tool to improve protein-ligand docking and screening accuracies by incorporating a scoring function correction term (SFCT) based on the OnionNet architecture.

name: PointDE
one_line_profile: Protein docking evaluation using 3D point cloud neural networks
detailed_description: Official implementation of PointDE, a deep learning model that evaluates protein docking poses by representing them as 3D point clouds to predict the quality of the docking.

name: GatorAffinity
one_line_profile: Protein-ligand binding affinity prediction using synthetic structural data
detailed_description: A deep learning model designed to boost protein-ligand binding affinity prediction by leveraging large-scale synthetic structural data for training.

name: KinaseDocker2
one_line_profile: PyMOL plugin for kinase inhibitor binding and affinity prediction
detailed_description: A PyMOL plugin and Docker-based tool specifically designed for predicting the binding modes and affinity of kinase inhibitors.

name: protein_mutation_scoring
one_line_profile: Scoring functions for protein mutation effects using ESM-2
detailed_description: A collection of scoring functions leveraging the ESM-2 protein language model to predict the effects of mutations on protein sequences.

name: protein-ligand-GNN
one_line_profile: GNN-based protein-ligand interaction prediction and XAI
detailed_description: Code implementation for analyzing protein-ligand interactions using Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) and Explainable AI (XAI) techniques.

name: iScore
one_line_profile: Machine learning-based scoring function for de novo drug discovery
detailed_description: Implementation of iScore, a machine learning-based scoring function designed to evaluate compounds in de novo drug discovery pipelines.

name: Generalized-Score-Functions-for-Causal-Discovery
one_line_profile: Generalized score-based method for causal discovery
detailed_description: A MATLAB implementation of generalized score functions for causal discovery, enabling the identification of causal structures from data.

name: NeoBert
one_line_profile: Neoantigen-HLA binding affinity prediction using BERT
detailed_description: A BERT-based deep learning model specifically designed to predict the binding affinity between neoantigens and HLA molecules, integrating biological features.

name: BINDKIN
one_line_profile: Benchmark for kinase-ligand interaction point mutations
detailed_description: A structural benchmark dataset and toolset for measuring the impact of point mutations on kinase-ligand interactions.

name: BACPI
one_line_profile: Bi-directional attention neural network for compound-protein interaction
detailed_description: A deep learning model using bi-directional attention mechanisms to predict compound-protein interactions and binding affinity.

name: ms2rescore
one_line_profile: AI-assisted rescoring of peptide identifications in proteomics
detailed_description: A modular platform for AI-assisted rescoring of peptide identifications from mass spectrometry data, improving identification rates.

name: spectrum_similarity
one_line_profile: Scoring functions for comparing MS/MS spectra
detailed_description: A library of scoring functions designed to calculate the similarity between mass spectrometry (MS/MS) spectra.

name: fpocket
one_line_profile: Fast protein pocket detection algorithm based on Voronoi tessellation
detailed_description: A very fast open source protein pocket detection algorithm based on Voronoi tessellation, widely used for identifying binding sites and extracting pocket descriptors.

name: IPSAE
one_line_profile: Scoring function for interprotein interactions in AlphaFold models
detailed_description: A scoring function designed to evaluate interprotein interactions within structures predicted by AlphaFold2 and AlphaFold3.

name: RNAdvisor
one_line_profile: Integrated wrapper for RNA 3D structure evaluation metrics
detailed_description: A docker-based wrapper that integrates multiple metrics and scoring functions for the evaluation of RNA 3D structures.

name: plif_validity
one_line_profile: Tool for assessing interaction recovery of predicted protein-ligand poses
detailed_description: Code and notebooks for assessing the interaction recovery of predicted protein-ligand poses, useful for validating docking results.

name: MD-IFP
one_line_profile: MD trajectory analysis using protein-ligand Interaction Fingerprints
detailed_description: A tool for analyzing Molecular Dynamics (MD) trajectories by calculating and monitoring protein-ligand Interaction Fingerprints (IFPs) over time.

name: pocketoptimizer
one_line_profile: Binding pocket optimization using force fields and scoring functions
detailed_description: A tool for optimizing binding pockets based on force fields and docking scoring functions to improve ligand binding prediction.

name: dock2interaction_profile
one_line_profile: Batch analysis of protein-ligand interactions from docking results
detailed_description: A script wrapper around PLIP to perform batch analysis of protein-ligand interactions derived from Smina/Vina docking results.

name: CaFE_Plugin
one_line_profile: VMD plugin for binding affinity prediction using free energy methods
detailed_description: A VMD plugin that facilitates binding affinity prediction using end-point free energy methods such as MM/PBSA or MM/GBSA.

name: otter-knowledge
one_line_profile: Knowledge-enhanced representation for drug target binding affinity prediction
detailed_description: A method that enriches protein sequence and SMILES drug databases with a large Knowledge Graph to improve drug target binding affinity prediction.

name: MGDTA
one_line_profile: Multigranular representation learning for drug-target binding affinity prediction
detailed_description: A deep learning model that explores multigranular representations to predict drug-target binding affinity, aiding in virtual screening and drug discovery.

name: DeepDTAF
one_line_profile: Deep learning architecture for protein-ligand binding affinity prediction
detailed_description: A deep learning framework that utilizes local and global features of proteins and ligands to predict binding affinity, supporting structure-based drug design.

name: AutoSF
one_line_profile: Automated search for bilinear scoring functions in knowledge graph learning
detailed_description: An automated machine learning (AutoML) tool designed to search for effective bilinear scoring functions for knowledge graph embedding, optimizing performance on link prediction tasks.

name: ERAS
one_line_profile: Efficient relation-aware scoring function search for knowledge graphs
detailed_description: A framework for efficiently searching for relation-aware scoring functions in knowledge graph embeddings, improving upon standard AutoML methods for KGE.

name: SCORE (SLAM)
one_line_profile: Saturated Consensus Relocalization in Semantic Line Maps
detailed_description: A robotics algorithm for relocalization in semantic line maps using saturated consensus, applicable in SLAM (Simultaneous Localization and Mapping) tasks.

name: GPCNDTA
one_line_profile: Drug-target binding affinity prediction using cross-attention networks
detailed_description: A model for predicting drug-target binding affinity that integrates graph features and pharmacophores via cross-attention networks.

name: Seeing Without Looking
one_line_profile: Contextual rescoring of object detections for AP maximization

name: spyrmsd
one_line_profile: Python tool for symmetry-corrected RMSD calculation in molecular structures
detailed_description: spyrmsd is a Python library for calculating Root-Mean-Square Deviation (RMSD) between molecular structures. It specifically handles symmetry correction, making it essential for accurately comparing ligand poses in docking and molecular dynamics.

name: rmsd
one_line_profile: Lightweight tool to calculate Root-Mean-Square Deviation (RMSD) between two molecular structures
detailed_description: This tool calculates the Root-Mean-Square Deviation (RMSD) of two molecules in XYZ or PDB format. It supports rotation (superposition) to find the minimum RMSD, a critical metric for validating docking poses.

name: Apobind
one_line_profile: Dataset of apo structures for protein-ligand complexes
detailed_description: Apobind provides a curated collection of apo (unbound) protein structures corresponding to the protein-ligand complexes found in the PDBbind database, useful for docking validation.

name: Muview2
one_line_profile: Visualization tool for micromagnetic simulations
detailed_description: Muview2 is a 3D visualization tool designed for rendering micromagnetic simulation data generated by Mumax or OOMMF software.

name: rmsd-tool
one_line_profile: Tool for calculating RMSD between molecular structures
detailed_description: A Fortran-based tool from the Grimme Lab to calculate the Root Mean Square Deviation (RMSD) between molecular structures, essential for structural comparison.

name: BM5-clean
one_line_profile: Cleaned Docking Benchmark 5 dataset
detailed_description: A cleaned version of the Docking Benchmark 5 (BM5) dataset, ready for use with HADDOCK and other docking protocols for validation purposes.

name: MemCplxDB
one_line_profile: Membrane protein complexes docking benchmark
detailed_description: A benchmark dataset specifically for membrane protein complexes, used to evaluate docking algorithms on membrane-embedded systems.

name: Prot-DNABenchmark
one_line_profile: Protein-DNA docking benchmark dataset
detailed_description: A benchmark dataset for evaluating protein-DNA docking methods, maintained by the HADDOCK team.

name: cyclic-peptides
one_line_profile: Cyclic peptide-protein complexes benchmark
detailed_description: A benchmark dataset containing cyclic peptide-protein complexes, including associated scripts and data for docking validation.

name: PoseBusters EM
one_line_profile: Energy minimization module for PoseBusters
detailed_description: A post-processing tool for energy minimization of molecular poses, used as part of the PoseBusters validation suite.

name: CasFinder
one_line_profile: CRISPR-Cas systems models for MacSyFinder
detailed_description: A collection of HMM profiles and model definitions for detecting CRISPR-Cas systems using the MacSyFinder tool.

name: protein-ligand-benchmark
one_line_profile: Benchmark dataset for free energy calculations
detailed_description: A curated benchmark dataset maintained by the Open Force Field Initiative for evaluating protein-ligand binding free energy calculations.

name: antibody_benchmark
one_line_profile: Antibody-Antigen Docking and Affinity Benchmark
detailed_description: A standard benchmark dataset for evaluating antibody-antigen docking and affinity prediction methods, maintained by the Pierce Lab.

name: muv
one_line_profile: Generator for Maximum Unbiased Validation (MUV) datasets in virtual screening
detailed_description: A Python tool designed to generate Maximum Unbiased Validation (MUV) datasets for benchmarking virtual screening methods. It implements algorithms to select active and decoy molecules that are topologically distinct but share similar physical properties, thereby removing artificial enrichment bias and providing a rigorous standard for validating docking and scoring functions.
